      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is Advarra or Nexrial better for a small independent site?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Advarra's CTMS products (OnCore and Clinical Conductor) are primarily designed for academic medical centers, health systems, and large site networks — not independent small research sites. Nexrial is purpose-built for independent sites running 5–25 concurrent studies with a CTMS budget under $700/month. If you are an independent site, Nexrial is likely the more appropriate evaluation; if you are an academic cancer center or large health system, Advarra is worth evaluating."
