  <section class="why-now-section">
    <h2>What each one actually is</h2>

    <h3>Nexrial — CTMS for independent research sites</h3>
    <p>
      Nexrial is a site-operations CTMS for independent research sites and small site
      networks running 5–25 concurrent studies. Verified native capabilities include:
      subject tracking with visit scheduling, delegation log with PI e-signature and
      PDF export, monitoring visit management (findings, action items), IRB submission
      tracking, protocol deviation logging, SOP management with version gating, training
      log with expiry tracking, consent version tracking, invoice management, and a
      21 CFR Part 11 immutable audit trail enforced by three independent database-level
      defenses.
    </p>
    <p>
      Pricing is published: <strong>$299/month Core, $599/month Pro</strong>, plus a
      Founding Site Program — 50% off for life for the first 3–5 sites ($149 Core / $299 Pro).
      No sales call required to evaluate cost.
    </p>

    <h3>Advarra — enterprise research technology platform</h3>
    <p>
      Advarra is an enterprise clinical research technology and services company. Its
      CTMS offerings are:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>OnCore CTMS</strong> — built for academic medical centers and cancer
        centers with comprehensive operations, financial management, regulatory
        management, and analytics. 88% of NCI-designated cancer centers use Advarra
        technology.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Clinical Conductor CTMS</strong> — built for site networks, health
        systems, and multi-site independent organizations. Supports financial oversight,
        patient recruitment, and research portfolio management. Add-on modules include
        CCText (HIPAA-compliant participant messaging), CCPay (subject reimbursements
        via debit card), and Epic EHR integration.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Advarra also offers eReg (regulatory document management), eSource (data
      capture), and Braid (AI analytics). The company serves approximately 3,500
      institutions and 50,000 investigators.
    </p>
    <p>
      Advarra pricing for all CTMS products is not publicly listed. Contact Advarra
      directly for a quote.
      <!-- Source: advarra.com/solutions-for/clinical-trial-sites/clinical-conductor-ctms/ and /solutions-for/clinical-trial-sites/ fetched 2026-04-23 -->
    </p>
