  <section class="why-now-section">
    <h2>FAQ</h2>

    <h3>Does Advarra's eReg replace the need for a CTMS regulatory binder?</h3>
    <p>
      Advarra sells eReg as a separate product from Clinical Conductor CTMS. eReg
      handles regulatory document management (ISF, binder templates, e-signatures on
      regulatory documents). Nexrial includes a regulatory binder with document
      versioning and audit trail as a native CTMS feature — no separate product
      required for basic regulatory document management.
    </p>

    <h3>Does Nexrial implement 21 CFR Part 11 controls?</h3>
    <p>
      Nexrial is designed against the controls of 21 CFR Part 11 Subpart B (electronic
      records). Audit-log integrity is enforced by three independent database-level
      defenses: UPDATE, DELETE, and TRUNCATE are revoked at the database user level,
      ensuring audit records cannot be modified even by application code. A full
      validation package (VAL-PLAN, IQ/OQ/PQ, VAL-REPORT) with executed-run evidence
      is available under NDA. Part 11 is a design standard, not a certification — see
      <a href="https://nexrial.com/trust">nexrial.com/trust</a> for the current control posture.
    </p>

    <h3>Can a small site use Advarra's Clinical Conductor?</h3>
    <p>
      Clinical Conductor is marketed to site networks and health systems. A small
      independent site can inquire with Advarra, but the platform scope (Epic integration,
      CCPay, CCText, enterprise portfolio reporting) and procurement process are oriented
      toward larger organizations. Sites with fewer than 25 concurrent studies and a
      CTMS budget under $700/month are likely outside Clinical Conductor's target profile.
    </p>

    <h3>Does Advarra provide IRB services as well as CTMS?</h3>
    <p>
      Yes. Advarra operates as a central IRB (Institutional Review Board) service in
      addition to its technology products. This vertical integration — IRB, CTMS, eReg,
      eSource — is a differentiator for health systems that want a single clinical
      research vendor. Nexrial does not offer IRB services; it is a CTMS point solution.
    </p>
  </section>

